Impax Asset Management Group - Wikipedia






















 






Impax Asset Management Group

From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia


					Jump to:					navigation, 					search


Impax Asset Management Group plc





Type

Public Company


Traded as
IPX


Industry
Investment Management


Founded
London, 1998


Headquarters
London, United Kingdom



Number of locations

London, New York, Portland, Hong Kong



Key people


Chairman - Keith Falconer Chief Executive - Ian Simm[1] CFO - Charlie Ridge MD, Co-Head of Listed Equity - Bruce Jenkyn-Jones[2] MD, Co-Head of Listed Equity - Hubert Aarts [3] MD Private Equity - Peter Rossbach [4] MD Private Equity- Daniel von Preyss [5]
MD Global Head of Marketing & Client Service - David Richardson [6]


AUM
£5.5 billion (as of 28 February 2017)


Website
www.impaxam.com


Impax Asset Management Group plc (LSE: IPX) is a specialist asset manager founded in 1998 investing in solutions to resource scarcity (in energy efficiency, alternative energy, water, waste, food and agriculture[7] and related sectors).
Impax Asset Management has been awarded a Queen’s Award for Enterprise: Sustainable Development, the UK’s highest business accolade for business success.[8]
Investments[edit]
Impax manages approximately £6.7 billion (as at 30 June 2017[9]) for institutional and high-net-worth investors globally, and is committed to providing strong long-term risk-adjusted returns.
The head office is in London with offices in New York City, Oregon and Hong Kong.
The Listed Equity team manages six global and regional investment strategies and manages listed equity funds on behalf of third party distributors including BNP Paribas[10]
The Private Equity team invests in European renewable power generation infrastructure assets in two funds: Impax New Energy Investors is a €125 million fund which closed in August 2006[11] and Impax New Energy Investors II is a €330 million fund which closed in August 2011.[12] The Climate Property Fund focuses on developing sustainable and energy efficient commercial property, primarily in the UK, adding synergistically to Impax's wider real asset investment strategy within private markets [13]
Partners and memberships[edit]
Impax partners FTSE Group to develop and manage the classification system underpinning the FTSE Environmental Markets Index Series.
Impax is a member of, or signatory to:

United Nations Principles for Responsible Investment (UNPRI)
UK Stewardship Code[14]
UK Sustainable Investment and Finance Association (UKSIF)[15]
The Carbon Disclosure Project (CDP)
Institutional Investors Group on Climate Change (IIGCC)
Investor Network on Climate Risk (INCR)
Forest Footprint Disclosure Project (FFD)[16]
US Sustainable investment and finance association (USSIF)[17]
The Global Impact Investing Network (GIIN)[18]
PRI Montreal Pledge[19]

