                "Impax Asset Management are investment innovators recognizing that the environmental challenges of our times can also be viewed through the lenses of business opportunities. What we like best about this resource optimization mandate is the versatility it can offer clients. From an environmental solution to an infrastructure play it also provides an alternative to the resource sector; many clients will find this fund a great diversifier for their portfolio."
            
- Daniel Solomon, Chief Investment Officer, NEI Investments


Company Profile

                Founded in 1998, Impax Asset Management Ltd. is an institutional asset manager with specialist expertise in the areas of resource efficiency and environmental markets. Their investment discipline is routed in a multidisciplinary team approach built out of an extensive global network of offices in New York, London, Hong Kong and Portland, Oregon.
                

                    Impax Asset Management is focused on emerging global investment opportunities in rapidly expanding sustainable investment markets.
                


Investment Approach

                The Impax Asset Management investment approach is forward looking and based on a sustainable outlook for the global economy that centers around resource optimization. Powerful undercurrents of increasing populations, pollution and finite resources require optimal use of resources moving forward. This will drive long-term business innovation and global investment opportunities.
                

                    Impax employs a Growth at a Reasonable Price (GARP) bottom up stock selection process. It begins with a proprietary resource optimization screen of the sustainable global investment universe. Quantitative financial metrics scoring, qualitative business assessment and an integrated ESG process are all utilized to uncover global stocks with long-term intrinsic value. A robust 10 step due diligence analysis ensure s high conviction stocks that are positioned to benefit from the favorable policy environment and potential performance drivers, such as M&A activity. Top down macro views for sustainable sectors and sub-sectors direct portfolio weightings.
                













