Frequently Asked Questions for Roper Technologies (NYSE:ROP)
What is Roper Technologies' stock symbol?

Roper Technologies trades on the New York Stock Exchange (NYSE) under the ticker symbol "ROP."



How often does Roper Technologies pay dividends? What is the dividend yield for Roper Technologies?

Roper Technologies declared a quarterly dividend on Monday, June 12th. Shareholders of record on Friday, July 7th will be given a dividend of $0.35 per share on Friday, July 21st. This represents a $1.40 annualized dividend and a yield of 0.60%. The ex-dividend date is Wednesday, July 5th.  View Roper Technologies' Dividend History.



How were Roper Technologies' earnings last quarter?

Roper Technologies, Inc. (NYSE:ROP) posted its earnings results on Monday, July, 25th. The company reported $1.56 earnings per share (EPS) for the quarter, missing the consensus estimate of $1.61 by $0.05. The firm earned $932 million during the quarter, compared to the consensus estimate of $948.22 million. Roper Technologies had a net margin of 16.74% and a return on equity of 12.81%. The business's revenue was up 5.0% compared to the same quarter last year. During the same period in the prior year, the business earned $1.70 EPS.  View Roper Technologies' Earnings History.



Where is Roper Technologies' stock going? Where will Roper Technologies' stock price be in 2017?

9 analysts have issued twelve-month price targets for Roper Technologies' stock. Their forecasts range from $175.00 to $268.00. On average, they anticipate Roper Technologies' share price to reach $233.22 in the next year. View Analyst Ratings for Roper Technologies.



