Frequently Asked Questions for Bemis Company (NYSE:BMS)
What is Bemis Company's stock symbol?

Bemis Company trades on the New York Stock Exchange (NYSE) under the ticker symbol "BMS."



How often does Bemis Company pay dividends? What is the dividend yield for Bemis Company?

Bemis Company announced a quarterly dividend on Thursday, May 4th. Investors of record on Wednesday, May 17th will be given a dividend of $0.30 per share on Thursday, June 1st. This represents a $1.20 annualized dividend and a yield of 2.82%. The ex-dividend date of this dividend is Monday, May 15th.  View Bemis Company's Dividend History.



How were Bemis Company's earnings last quarter?

Bemis Company, Inc. (NYSE:BMS) posted its quarterly earnings data on Thursday, July, 27th. The company reported $0.48 earnings per share (EPS) for the quarter, missing the Zacks' consensus estimate of $0.56 by $0.08. The business had revenue of $1.01 billion for the quarter, compared to analysts' expectations of $1.03 billion. Bemis Company had a net margin of 5.73% and a return on equity of 19.95%. Bemis Company's revenue was down .9% compared to the same quarter last year. During the same period last year, the firm posted $0.67 EPS.  View Bemis Company's Earnings History.



What guidance has Bemis Company issued on next quarter's earnings?

Bemis Company updated its FY17 earnings guidance on Thursday, July, 27th. The company provided EPS guidance of $2.35-2.50 for the period, compared to the Thomson Reuters consensus estimate of $2.55. 



Where is Bemis Company's stock going? Where will Bemis Company's stock price be in 2017?

9 equities research analysts have issued twelve-month price objectives for Bemis Company's shares. Their predictions range from $41.00 to $54.00. On average, they anticipate Bemis Company's stock price to reach $48.88 in the next twelve months. View Analyst Ratings for Bemis Company.



Who are some of Bemis Company's key competitors?

 Some companies that are related to Bemis Company include Allegion PLC (ALLE), The Middleby Corporation (MIDD), BPC Acquisition Corp (BERY), Nordson Corporation (NDSN), Hubbell (HUBB), HD Supply Holdings (HDS), Graco (GGG), Donaldson Company (DCI), AGCO Corporation (AGCO), Lincoln Electric Holdings (LECO), Zebra Technologies Corporation (ZBRA), Flowserve Corporation (FLS), Reliance Steel & Aluminum Co. (RS), AptarGroup (ATR), Colfax Corporation (CFX), Sonoco Products Company (SON), Metso Oyj (MXCYY) and MSC Industrial Direct Company (MSM).



