						Financial Comparison: RBC Bearings (ROLL) versus NN (NASDAQ:NNBR)					

						 July 15th, 2017  - 0 comments - Filed Under -
 by Latisha Jones 


							Filed Under: Comparison Articles - Finance 







Tweet










NN (NASDAQ: NNBR) and RBC Bearings (NASDAQ:ROLL) are both industrial products companies, but which is the superior stock? We will compare the two companies based on the strength of their analyst recommendations, earnings, profitabiliy, valuation, risk, institutional ownership and dividends. 
Volatility & Risk
NN has a beta of 0.63, meaning that its share price is 37% less volatile than the S&P 500. Comparatively, RBC Bearings has a beta of 1.3, meaning that its share price is 30% more volatile than the S&P 500. 




Dividends
NN pays an annual dividend of $0.28 per share and has a dividend yield of 1.0%. RBC Bearings does not pay a dividend. NN pays out 45.9% of its earnings in the form of a dividend. 
Earnings & Valuation
This table compares NN and RBC Bearings’ revenue, earnings per share and valuation.



